// bug #73 (FIXED 2026-07-15): reassigning a GLOBAL Array<T> grown
// element-by-element used to leak every intermediate COW buffer on LLVM
// native — superseded global-slot payloads were never released in the
// escaping-tier bump heap, giving O(N²) live bytes for O(N) data and dying
// `lvrt: heap exhausted` near N≈10k. Fix: LlvmGen StoreGlobal now releases
// the old global value before storing the new one (mirrors the RawSet
// field release-old/retain-new path). N=10000 now completes on every
// engine; peak drops from 256 MiB exhaustion to ~525 KB. Regression guard.
Array<int> xs;

void build(int n) {
    int i = 0;
    while (i < n) {
        xs = xs.add(i);
        i = i + 1;
    }
}

build(10000);
console.writeln(xs.length().toString());
